## Isolation guarantees per agent

| Shared resource | Isolation mechanism |
|---|---|
| Solver job queue | Semaphore serializes — agents naturally queue |
| Payload staging file | Each agent uses `/tmp/payload-<TC_ID>.json` |
| `planner_output` rows | Keyed by auto-generated `plan_id` |
| `planner_assignments` rows | Keyed by `plan_id` |
| Checkpoints | `{job_id}_partition_*.json` — `job_id` unique |
| Docker logs | Every line carries `job_id` — grep-per-agent |
| Solver stdout buffer | Agent records `--since` timestamp at submit, greps that window |
| State tracker doc | ONLY the main session writes it; agents return report, main session appends |

There is **no write path** where two agents can touch the same file or
DB row. Read verification queries use `plan_id` filters. The state
tracker doc is written exclusively by the main session.

