## Round 1 — P0 critical path

**Scope:** TC-01 (baseline regression), TC-02 (primary activation).

**Dispatch order:** strictly serial — TC-01 first, gate, then TC-02.

**Why serial, not parallel:** if TC-01 fails (baseline broken), running
TC-02 is waste. The baseline must prove the Phase K gate doesn't break
legacy callers before we validate the new path.

| TC | Payload | Time budget | Gate if fails |
|---|---|---|---|
| TC-01 | T-BASE | 2.5h hard cap | HALT suite — baseline regressed |
| TC-02 | T-BOTH | 2.5h hard cap | HALT suite — core feature broken |

**Each agent does:** submit → poll → V-1, V-2, V-6 (TC-01 adds V-3/V-4
for TC-02) → report.

**Post-round:** main session updates `CT_RT_TEST_STATE.md` with
`plan_id`, `job_id`, PASS/FAIL, observed distribution.

