## Round 2 — P1 deep coverage

**Scope:** TC-03 (RT-only), TC-04 (CT-only), TC-05 (cross-month
proration), TC-10 (analyzer warning).

**Dispatch order:** strictly serial (solver semaphore = 1). TC-03 and
TC-04 are quick-ish (month-long range), TC-05 is the longest (cross
three months, may partition), TC-10 depends on a resource with NO
RT/CT source data.

**Dependencies:**

- TC-03, TC-04, TC-05 are independent — any order works. Suggest TC-03
  → TC-04 → TC-05 (size ascending).
- **TC-10 has a data precondition**: a resource must exist with no RT
  or CT calendar absences in the plan range. Pre-flight step added:
  before dispatching TC-10, the main session queries external DB for
  a candidate (query in test-cases doc §V-5) and injects the
  `resource_id` into the agent prompt via `target_team_ids` /
  `target_group_ids` narrowing, OR by instructing the agent to filter
  the trigger to a single team containing that resource.

| TC | Payload | Time budget | Gate if fails |
|---|---|---|---|
| TC-03 | T-RT | 2.5h | Log FAIL, continue round |
| TC-04 | T-CT | 2.5h | Log FAIL, continue round |
| TC-05 | T-CROSS | 2.5h | Log FAIL, continue round (partition carryover is next-test-only concern) |
| TC-10 | Modified T-BOTH (narrowed scope) | 1h | Log FAIL — analyzer warning path regressed |

**Round gate:** proceed to Round 3 if ≥3/4 passed. Otherwise halt for
triage.

