## Round 3 — P2 edge cases

**Scope:** TC-06 (short range), TC-07 (lock_allocations=false), TC-08
(re-run stability), TC-09 (transition baseline→activation).

**Dispatch order:** mostly serial, but two of these are **composites**
that must run as a SINGLE agent dispatch (not split across agents):

- TC-08 = "Run TC-02, then TC-02 again" — one agent submits two
  triggers sequentially using `/tmp/payload-tc08-a.json` and
  `/tmp/payload-tc08-b.json`, compares results. Between the two
  triggers it confirms the checkpoint from run A persists.
- TC-09 = "T-BASE then T-BOTH" — one agent, two triggers, compares
  before/after assignment_type distribution.

TC-06 and TC-07 are single-payload tests (one agent each).

| TC | Payload | Agent model | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| TC-06 | T-SHORT | Single-payload agent | Fast — `time_limit_seconds: 1800`, may finish in <5 min |
| TC-07 | T-UNLOCKED | Single-payload agent | Confirms Phase A flag derivation gates on `lock_allocations` |
| TC-08 | T-BOTH x 2 | Composite agent | One agent runs two triggers back-to-back |
| TC-09 | T-BASE → T-BOTH | Composite agent | One agent runs two triggers back-to-back |

**Round gate:** proceed to Round 4 if ≥3/4 passed.

