## Agent prompt template (single-payload test)

The main session dispatches one of these per test case in Rounds 1–2
and for single-payload tests in Rounds 3–4.

```
Task: execute <TC_ID> <short title>.

Goal: <one sentence, from test-cases doc test-matrix row>.

Inputs:
  SOLVER_URL       = http://localhost:8005/qa/planner/api/v1/solver/trigger
  JOBS_URL         = http://localhost:8005/qa/planner/api/v1/solver/jobs
  READS_URL        = http://localhost:8003/qa/ai/api/v1
  SOLVER_CONTAINER = <pre-flight fixture>
  TEST_RESOURCE_ID = <pre-flight fixture>
  PAYLOAD_FILE     = /tmp/payload-<TC_ID>.json
  PAYLOAD_JSON     = <inlined JSON from test-cases doc>
  EXPECTED_OUTCOMES: <inlined bullet list from test-cases doc>
  TIME_BUDGET      = <per-table>
  VERIFICATION     = [list of V-ids to run]

Procedure:
  1. Write PAYLOAD_JSON to PAYLOAD_FILE.
  2. Record submission timestamp: SUBMIT_TS=$(date +%s).
  3. POST to SOLVER_URL, record job_id.
  4. Poll JOBS_URL/{job_id} every 30s until status in {COMPLETE, FAILED}.
     Hard cap: TIME_BUDGET. If exceeded, return TIMEOUT failure.
  5. Extract plan_id.
  6. Run each V-<id> from VERIFICATION (URLs in test-cases doc).
  7. Grep logs: docker logs $SOLVER_CONTAINER --since $SUBMIT_TS 2>&1 | grep $job_id.

Return (<400 words):
  - VERDICT: PASS | FAIL | TIMEOUT
  - plan_id, job_id
  - V-2 distribution JSON
  - Any expected log signature missing
  - If FAIL: closest matching line from log output + recommended phase to
    inspect (from changelog).

Do not edit any files outside /tmp. Do not rebuild containers.
Do not modify MAX_CONCURRENT_JOBS.
```

