## What NOT to do

- ❌ Do not `docker compose down` mid-suite — kills the shared QA
  stack.
- ❌ Do not dispatch agents in parallel — solver serializes anyway and
  you lose the gate.
- ❌ Do not edit `MAX_CONCURRENT_JOBS` — user declined.
- ❌ Do not re-use `/tmp/payload.json` across agents — each gets a
  unique filename.
- ❌ Do not read raw `docker logs` in the main session — delegate to
  agents and only consume summaries.
- ❌ Do not skip Round 0 — if schema missing, entire suite fails
  identically and wastes 20+ hours.
- ❌ Do not proceed past a failed round gate without user sign-off.
- ❌ Do not run N-5 (rebuild test) until all other tests in Round 4
  have completed.
- ❌ Do not have an agent write to `CT_RT_TEST_STATE.md` — ONLY the
  main session updates it (concurrency hazard).

